# CampuGrid — Task Tracker

## Phase 1 — Foundation (Week 1–2)

- [ ] Docker Compose infra (Postgres, Redis, MinIO, Registry, Prometheus, Grafana, Loki)
- [ ] FastAPI project skeleton (config, health endpoint, CORS, lifespan events)
- [ ] SQLAlchemy models + Alembic initial migration (all 6 tables)
- [ ] Pydantic schemas (request/response for all endpoints)
- [ ] Redis service (connection pool, heartbeat registry, queue helpers)
- [ ] MinIO service (upload, download, presigned URLs, bucket management)
- [ ] WebSocket connection manager (room-based broadcasting)
- [ ] User auth (JWT + OAuth2 Google SSO)
- [ ] Node registration endpoint (POST /api/v1/nodes/register)
- [ ] Heartbeat handler (WebSocket heartbeat → Redis sorted set)
- [ ] Job submission endpoint (POST /api/v1/jobs)

## Phase 2 — AI Pipeline + Rendering (Week 3–4)

- [ ] Magic bytes detector
- [ ] Blend file analyzer (blend_file_reader)
- [ ] Python AST analyzer (import scanning, framework detection)
- [ ] Image catalog (Tier 1 pre-defined configs)
- [ ] Chunk splitter (frame-range for render, byte-range for data)
- [ ] Pipeline orchestrator (Celery task chain)
- [ ] Event-driven scheduler (on-chunk-queued dispatch)
- [ ] Contributor Python daemon (agent, heartbeat, executor, storage bridge)
- [ ] Storage bridge (MinIO ↔ local volume for --network none)
- [ ] Render assembler (FFmpeg frame stitching)
- [ ] Build Blender Docker image

## Phase 3 — Fault Tolerance + Data Processing (Week 5–6)

- [ ] Watchdog (30s Celery beat, stale node detection, chunk rescue)
- [ ] Reliability scoring (degradation/recovery)
- [ ] Data processing splitter (CSV byte-range sharding)
- [ ] Data assembler (merge output shards)
- [ ] Gemini Dockerfile verifier (Tier 2: verify + adapt)
- [ ] Gemini Dockerfile generator (Tier 3: full gen, cached)
- [ ] Kaniko builder (trigger build, track status)
- [ ] Build python-data Docker image

## Phase 4 — ML Training + Simulation (Week 7–8)

- [ ] Docker overlay network manager
- [ ] Auto-checkpoint injection (monkey-patch PyTorch optimizer)
- [ ] Local SGD implementation
- [ ] DDP orchestration (torchrun setup)
- [ ] ML splitter (dataset row sharding)
- [ ] ML assembler (best weights, training curves)
- [ ] Simulation splitter (domain decomposition)
- [ ] Simulation assembler (domain reconstruction)
- [ ] Build PyTorch + OpenFOAM Docker images
- [ ] ML sync mode selection (Standard vs Premium pricing)

## Phase 5 — Consumer Web App (Week 8–9)

- [ ] Next.js project setup (App Router, TailwindCSS, NextAuth)
- [ ] Auth flow (Google OAuth)
- [ ] Submit page (drag-drop + live AI detection stream)
- [ ] Price comparison widget
- [ ] Monitor page (live chunk cards with GPU bars)
- [ ] Results page (download, preview, training curves)
- [ ] WebSocket integration (real-time updates hook)

## Phase 6 — Contributor Tauri App (Week 9–10)

- [ ] Tauri project setup (Tauri + Svelte, system tray)
- [ ] Docker installer integration
- [ ] NVIDIA detection
- [ ] Registration flow
- [ ] Dashboard view (GPU meter, earnings, active job)
- [ ] Settings view (resource limits, schedule)
- [ ] History view (past jobs)
- [ ] Leaderboard view (campus rankings)
- [ ] Billing engine (per-chunk pricing, dynamic multiplier)
- [ ] Gamification (credits, ranks, streaks)
- [ ] PyInstaller bundle for Python daemon

## Phase 7 — Marketing Site + Polish (Week 10–11)

- [ ] Landing page (hero, features, how-it-works, pricing)
